						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Chennakēśavasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>VILAMBI.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in cyclic year Viḷaṁbi, Māgha, ba. 10 and the characters of the inscription can be assigned to 16th century.</p>						

						<p>Records the obeisance <hi rend="italic">(sēva)</hi> of Mumaḍi Reḍḍi, son of Yanugu (Yēnugu) Māchi Reḍi to the god Chennakēśavamurti of Eṟṟaguḍi Nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
